################################################################

# MOTIVATIONS, DECISIONS, PRINCIPLES, EMOTIONS, CONFLICTS, THEMES, EVENTS

################################################################

:Motivation_RewardDefenderAndPunishTraitor
a :Motivation ;
:description "To honor the defender of the city and punish the traitor for the common good of the polis."^^xsd:string .

:MoralDecision_BuryEteoclesWithHonors
a :MoralDecision ;
:description "To bury Eteocles and grant him the proper rites and honors due to the city’s best fallen warrior."^^xsd:string .

:MoralDecision_DenyBurialToPolyneices
a :MoralDecision ;
:description "To forbid mourning and burial for Polyneices and leave his body unburied as a public disgrace, torn by animals."^^xsd:string .

:MoralDecision_HonorLoyalToCityLivingAndDead
a :MoralDecision ;
:description "To honor anyone who means well for the city, in death as in life."^^xsd:string .

:EthicalPrinciple_JusticeByMerit
a :EthicalPrinciple ;
:description "Honor and civic recognition should follow merit and service to the city."^^xsd:string .

:EthicalPrinciple_CivicLoyalty
a :EthicalPrinciple ;
:description "Goodwill and loyalty to the city are the basis for public honor."^^xsd:string .

:EthicalPrinciple_NoHonorForWickedOverJust
a :EthicalPrinciple ;
:description "Criminals must never be honored before law-abiding citizens."^^xsd:string .

:Emotion_SternResolve
a :Emotion ;
:description "Stern determination to enforce honor for the just and disgrace for the criminal."^^xsd:string .

:Conflict_HonorWickedVsJust
a :Conflict ;
:description "Tension between honoring the wicked and upholding honor for the law-abiding and just."^^xsd:string ;
:conflictBetween :EthicalPrinciple_NoHonorForWickedOverJust, :MoralDecision_BuryEteoclesWithHonors ;
:conflictBetween :EthicalPrinciple_NoHonorForWickedOverJust, :MoralDecision_DenyBurialToPolyneices .

:Theme_JusticeByMerit
a :Theme ;
:description "Public honor is distributed according to justice and merit: the defender is honored, the criminal is disgraced."^^xsd:string .

:Theme_PatriotismAndCivicLoyalty
a :Theme ;
:description "Civic loyalty defines worth; those who mean well for the city receive honor in life and death."^^xsd:string .

:Theme_BurialHonorAndDisgrace
a :Theme ;
:description "Burial rites and mourning are civic marks of honor; denial of burial is an extreme public disgrace."^^xsd:string .

:Theme_PunishmentOfTreason
a :Theme ;
:description "The would-be destroyer of the fatherland is punished through proclamation, dishonor, and exposure."^^xsd:string .

:Event_EteoclesDefendsCityDies
a owl:NamedIndividual, owl:Thing ;
:description "Eteocles dies fighting for the city as its foremost warrior."^^xsd:string ;
:relatedTo :MoralDecision_BuryEteoclesWithHonors ;
:relatedTo :Motivation_RewardDefenderAndPunishTraitor .

:Event_PolyneicesReturnsToDestroyCity
a owl:NamedIndividual, owl:Thing ;
:description "Polyneices returns from exile intending to burn his father’s land and harm his kin and citizens through bloodshed and enslavement."^^xsd:string ;
:relatedTo :MoralDecision_DenyBurialToPolyneices ;
:relatedTo :Motivation_RewardDefenderAndPunishTraitor .

:Event_CreonProclaimsDecree
a owl:NamedIndividual, owl:Thing ;
:description "Creon publicly proclaims the decree distinguishing honor for Eteocles and disgrace for Polyneices."^^xsd:string ;
:relatedTo :MoralDecision_BuryEteoclesWithHonors ;
:relatedTo :MoralDecision_DenyBurialToPolyneices ;
:relatedTo :MoralDecision_HonorLoyalToCityLivingAndDead .

:Event_EteoclesDefendsCityDies :relatedTo :Event_CreonProclaimsDecree .
:Event_PolyneicesReturnsToDestroyCity :relatedTo :Event_CreonProclaimsDecree .

